request.description:
### Update Mutations

This endpoint allows the user to update mutations for a specific experiment.

#### Request Body

- form-data

    - `mutation_pattern` (string): The mutation pattern to be assigned to the structure. (This field will be read first.)

    - `file` (file): The file containing the mutation data (A csv/xlsx/xls file with `clean_mut_wt` column in its first worksheet). **This field is read only if the** **`mutation_pattern`** **field is empty.**


#### Response

The response is in JSON format and follows the schema below:

``` json
{
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "id": {
      "type": "string"
    },
    "name": {
      "type": "string"
    },
    "email": {
      "type": "string"
    },
    "user_id": {
      "type": "string"
    },
    "is_successful": {
      "type": "boolean"
    },
    "message": {
      "type": "string"
    },
    "is_authenticated": {
      "type": "boolean"
    },
    "timestamp": {
      "type": "string"
    },
    "mutation_pattern": {
      "type": "string"
    },
    "mutant_string_list": {
      "type": "array",
      "items": {
        "type": "string"
      }
    }
  }
}

